abstract: The chairman of the Federal Communications Commission appears to have enough votes to pass an effort to ensure open access to Web sites and online services.
snippet: The chairman of the Federal Communications Commission appears to have enough votes to pass an effort to ensure open access to Web sites and online services.
lead_paragraph: 6:42 p.m. | Updated  The chairman of the Federal Communications Commission appears to have the votes he needs to pass new rules for net neutrality.

headline.main: F.C.C. Poised to Pass Net Neutrality Order
